OL,3,CBirmingham City Council leader claims
OL,4,Cauthority is no longer 'bankrupt'
OL,6,F"We are back in the mainstream of
OL,7,Flocal government. We have closed a
OL,8,F#300 million budget gap, we've tackled
OL,9,Four equal pay liabilities, and we are
OL,10,Fgetting to grips with improving the
OL,11,Fservices that the council provides for
OL,12,Fthe residents of Birmingham.
OL,14,F"This is an important milestone in our
OL,15,Fimprovement journey and we will
OL,16,Fcontinue to take the difficult
OL,17,Fdecisions required to be the council
OL,18,Fthe people of this city deserve.
