OL,3,CBirmingham City Council leader claims
OL,4,Cauthority is no longer 'bankrupt'
OL,6,F"I'm determined that the mistakes of
OL,7,Fthe past will not be repeated, as we
OL,8,Fdrive further efficiencies to deliver
OL,9,Fbetter services and value for money
OL,10,Ffor council taxpayers.
OL,12,F"I'm ambitious for Birmingham's
OL,13,Ffuture. Now we will step up our work
OL,14,Fwith West Midlands Mayor Richard
OL,15,FParker and Government to invest in our
OL,16,Fcommunities, delivering the homes,
OL,17,Fjobs and services that the people of
OL,18,Fthis city deserve."
